question: Where can I find more information about the tutoring and learning resources services available at UWF?
ground_truth: You can visit the Tutoring & Learning Resources website at http://uwf.edu/offices/advising-tutoring/ace/what-we-do/ for more information about services offered.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / Center for Academic Success / Tutoring & Learning Resources

question: How do I upload files to my personal Canvas file storage?
ground_truth: To upload files to your personal Canvas file storage, click the Account Icon in the left side navigation bar, locate and click the Files navigation link, and then click the Upload button to add files to your repository.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / eLearning / eLearning Help for Students / Canvas Orientation - Personal Settings / 4. Manage your Personal Files

question: What do I need to do before I can change my major at UWF?
ground_truth: Before changing a major, you must seek academic advisement from the department offering the new major. Your change of major cannot be processed without an Advisor approval. You should also review the University Catalog, visit the department website, run a 'what-if' Degree Works, and be aware of admission requirements for the new major. If you receive financial aid, you must check with the Financial Aid department regarding implications on your aid eligibility. If you are a student-athlete or veteran, you must also seek approval from an Athletic or Veteran Advisor in addition to the specific college Academic Advisor, Department Chair, or Dean.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / Majors / Programs / Program change requirements

question: How do I set up Eduroam on my Windows 11 laptop?
ground_truth: You can find Eduroam Setup Instructions for Windows 11 at https://confluence.uwf.edu/x/OoupBQ
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / Wireless Networks / Configuring Your Device for Eduroam

question: I'm a fully online student and haven't completed all my immunization requirements. How do I waive my immunizations?
ground_truth: Log into MyUWF and search for the Immunization Status app. Click the app. If you are in an online program and haven't met all immunization requirements, you can waive them. Select 'Yes' for the waive question, then agree to the waiver terms when prompted. Click proceed to complete the waiver and you will be brought to the main page indicating you have met your immunization requirements.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / Immunization Status / Waiving immunization requirements via MyUWF for online students

question: How do I review and approve course material adoptions that faculty members have submitted in Follett Discover?
ground_truth: Click the My Courses link to start reviewing all submitted adoptions awaiting your approval. Then click the Review This Course button within the course to review any materials awaiting approval. Click the Approve or Reject button for each material. Once a material has been approved, the adoption will be sent to the campus store for completion. If the material is rejected, the faculty will see that the title adoption status says Rejected by Institution.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / Textbook Adoption - Follett | Discover (Departmental Administrators)

question: How do I find my UWF ID number if I don't have my Nautilus card?
ground_truth: You can find your UWF ID number via MyUWF. Log in to MyUWF using your Argonet username and password, click your name at the top right, click 'My Account,' and your UWF ID number should be displayed. Alternatively, if you've received emails from UWF before, your UWF ID number may be at the bottom of some of those emails—you can search your email account for the phrase 'uwf id' to locate it.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / Nautilus Card / Locating your UWF ID number

question: How will I know when my students are able to schedule their ProctorU exam?
ground_truth: You will receive an email letting you know that your students will be able to schedule the exam after ProctorU has received and verified all exam information.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / Proctored Exams Options for Students / ProctorU - Faculty Instructions / Confirmation that your Exam has been Scheduled with ProctorU

question: What email address should I use when creating my Parchment account for ordering transcripts?
ground_truth: You should use a personal email address that is NOT affiliated with the University of West Florida. Using your UWF email address may cause issues accessing your transcripts after the downgrade of your ArgoNet account.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / Transcripts / Ordering an Official UWF Transcript

question: How many computers can I install Microsoft 365 on as a UWF student?
ground_truth: Each eligible student is entitled to install Microsoft 365 on up to five computers. Your subscription also allows Office Mobile for Android and/or Office Mobile for iOS on up to 5 mobile devices.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / Microsoft 365 Student Advantage

question: How do I request academic accommodations at UWF?
ground_truth: To request academic accommodations at UWF, you must follow three steps: (1) Apply and be admitted to the University of West Florida, (2) Self-identify by submitting an application and supporting medical documentation to verify your need for accommodations, and (3) Complete a registration appointment with a Student Accessibility Resources (SAR) staff member by calling 850.474.2387 to schedule.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / Student Accessibility Resources

question: What do I need to do if I want to add a course late in the semester?
ground_truth: To add a course late in the semester, you must submit a Request for Schedule Adjustment form to the Office of the Registrar during the second week of classes. The request must include a Reason for Request (which should only be due to university error), the course CRN, and confirmation that open seats are available. The request will be routed to the instructor and department chair for approval via signature. If your adjustment increases credit hours or fees, you must pay any additional fees immediately to avoid a $100 late payment fee.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / Registration / Requesting a Schedule Adjustment

question: What online tools can I use to meet with my group members for a class project?
ground_truth: You can use Canvas Conferences to meet with fellow group members within your Canvas Group site, or Google Meet if you have a Gmail account. Canvas Conferences is accessible via your Canvas Group site and allows you to create, start, and manage conferences with group members. Google Meet is available for those with Gmail accounts and allows you to create meetings for others to join by going to meet.google.com.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / eLearning / eLearning Help for Students / UWF Online Student Support Links and Resources / Successful Online Group Work / Real-time Communication Tools

question: How do I submit my EAD Card using the online form?
ground_truth: To submit your EAD Card, you must first log into www.my.uwf.edu. Then search for the EAD Card Upload Form or use the direct link to access it. Follow the form guidance to upload your EAD Card by selecting the type of EAD Card you are uploading. If you have multiple files for your EAD card upload, you can select them as needed.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / International Affairs / Application Guide and Resources for Optional Practical Training (OPT) / Submitting the EAD Card Upload Form

question: How can I provide feedback directly on student assignments in Canvas?
ground_truth: You can use SpeedGrader to provide comments directly on student PDFs, Word documents, and PowerPoints. SpeedGrader can be accessed from any assignment, quiz, or graded discussion, or directly from the Gradebook.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / eLearning / eLearning Help for Faculty / Canvas Help for Instructors / Speedgrader in Canvas

question: How do I arrange to use the AR Sandbox for my class?
ground_truth: You should check with the GIS Lab Manager to arrange a time to use the GIS Lab or have the sandbox moved to another location.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / GIS at UWF / GIS Technology / Augmented Reality Sandbox

question: What documentation do I need to provide to use my VA Educational benefits as a transient student at UWF?
ground_truth: To utilize VA Educational benefits as a transient (guest) student at UWF, you will need: 1) Certificate of Eligibility, 2) Florida Shine approval (if your institution is within the state of FL), 3) Parent letter from Primary School (typically provided by your primary school's veteran services office), and 4) VA Enrollment Certification Form (ECF) which you must fill out through your my.uwf.edu account after registering for classes.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / MVRC - VA Education benefits at UWF / MVRC - Getting Started / Transient student process

question: How can I get technical support if I'm having problems with eLearning or Canvas?
ground_truth: ITS offers support to online students via phone, online request form, and email for non-Canvas (eLearning) questions or problems. You can contact them at helpdesk@uwf.edu or 850.474.2075. Help Desk hours are Monday-Thursday 8:00am-7:00pm, Friday 8:00am-5:00pm, and they are closed Saturday-Sunday.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / eLearning / eLearning Help for Students / UWF Online Student Support Links and Resources

question: What do I need to do to ensure my mailing addresses meet the requirements for discounted bulk mail rates at UWF?
ground_truth: You must update addresses within 95 days prior to a mailing using the U.S. Postal Service 'Move Update' regulations. You can use CASS/DPV certified software through a mail service or print shop provider to validate and update your address list, or use manual methods within the last 95 days. The addresses must be certified and the Postage Statement must be signed certifying compliance under penalty of law.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / Postal and Passport Services / Address List Updates

question: Where can I get tutoring for my Calculus course, and how do I find out about the schedule?
ground_truth: Calculus Lab tutoring is located in Building 4, Room 321 and supports courses MAT1059, MAC2233, MAC2311, MAC2312, MAC2313, and MAP2302. For questions about the schedule, you can email mathstat@uwf.edu or visit the Calculus Lab Tutoring Website.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / Center for Academic Success / Tutoring & Learning Resources / Subject-based Tutoring Services / Other Available Tutoring

question: How do I check if I've submitted all my required immunization documents for UWF?
ground_truth: You can access the Immunization Status app via MyUWF by searching for 'immunization status.' The app will display a message at the top of the page indicating whether you have submitted all required immunization documents or if any requirements are missing.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / Immunization Status / Viewing Immunization Status in MyUWF

question: How do I get my study abroad coursework approved when studying at another Florida public university or college?
ground_truth: To get study abroad coursework approved for study at a Florida public university or college, you need to follow the Transient Student Process for Outgoing Transient Students. You should submit the Transient Student Form through Florida Shines and follow the process outlined by the UWF Registrar. You can find detailed instructions on the UWF Student Tutorial for Outgoing Transient Students page on the UWF Registrar website. Additionally, you should keep copies of all syllabi for courses taken abroad and email them to your academic advisors, as syllabi may be requested to confirm that a transfer course meets degree requirements.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / Study Abroad at UWF / Getting Your Study Abroad Courses Approved / Getting Your Other Florida University Study Abroad Courses Approved

question: What happens if I don't submit my verification documents by the deadline?
ground_truth: Failure to complete verification within the required time period will result in reduction, cancellation, or forfeit of federal, state, or most institutional aid.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / Financial Aid Verification Policy

question: How do I upload a syllabus for my course using the Syllabus App?
ground_truth: To upload a syllabus, access the Syllabus App through MyUWF and select 'Upload' from the menu in the header. Use the search UI to select a semester and enter your course number. Click the 'upload' button, then click 'Choose File' to select a PDF file. Finally, click the 'Upload' button and wait while the file is uploaded and attached to your course.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / Uploading a syllabus using the Syllabus App

question: How do I set up bookable appointments in Google Calendar for students to sign up for?
ground_truth: To set up bookable appointments in Google Calendar: 1) Go to your Google Calendar at calendar.google.com, 2) Click on Create in the upper left-hand corner, 3) Select Appointment schedule. From there you can set up your availability and share the calendar with people you want to be able to book your appointments with using the share button in the upper right-hand corner.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / Google Workspace / Creating Bookable Appointments in Google Calendar

question: Where can I find resources and support for accessibility accommodations at UWF?
ground_truth: UWF Student Accessibility Resources is available at https://uwf.edu/academic-engagement-and-student-affairs/departments/student-accessibility-resources/. This department provides accessibility support and accommodations for students.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / eLearning / eLearning Help for Students / Accessibility Resources for eLearning - Student

question: How do I view my unofficial transcript in MyUWF?
ground_truth: To view your unofficial transcript, log in to MyUWF, search for and select the Student Academic Records Menu app, click the My Academic Transcript link, select the appropriate transcript level from the drop-down box, choose "Unofficial Transcript" from the Transcript Type drop-down box, and your unofficial transcript should appear. You can right-click to print or save a PDF version.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / Transcripts / Viewing an Unofficial Transcript

question: I'm enrolling in the Family Nurse Practitioner program at UWF and planning to work in Texas after graduation. What do I need to do to make sure my degree will be accepted for licensure there?
ground_truth: You should contact the applicable licensure board in Texas prior to beginning the academic program to determine whether the UWF Family Nurse Practitioner program meets licensure requirements in that state. It is your responsibility to confirm program eligibility for licensure in any state outside Florida, as UWF cannot confirm whether the program meets requirements for professional licensure outside of Florida.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / UWF State Authorizations / Notification of State Licensures - GAD Admissions

question: I'm an undergraduate student and I want to enroll in 20 semester hours next semester. What do I need to do to make this happen?
ground_truth: To enroll for more than 18 semester hours in a semester, you must have written permission from your academic advisor and the chairperson of your major department. You should contact your advisor to complete the Adjustment to Minimum/Maximum Hours Dynamic Form. The form will route for the necessary signatures, including yours, and once signed, it will be submitted to the Office of the Registrar for processing. Only the Office of the Registrar may perform an override to the minimum/maximum hours restrictions.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / Registration / Understanding Minimum/Maximum Semester Hour Restrictions

question: How can I get help designing an event that will create meaningful behavior change for my attendees?
ground_truth: You can request an Event Design workshop from Patti Spaniola, Director of Conferences & Events. The workshop uses the #EventCanvas methodology to help identify stakeholders, understand their needs, determine desired behavior changes, and create a creative prototype for a successful event. Teams must have a minimum of 5 members and the workshop requires two 2.5-hour sessions conducted virtually via Zoom and Mural. Contact Patti at pspaniola@uwf.edu to schedule a custom workshop for your team.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / Conference & Event Planning Services

question: How do I find out who my assigned mentors are at UWF?
ground_truth: Log in to my.uwf.edu, enter 'advising' and click the 'Search' button, then click the 'Advising Status' link. Scroll down and below the Advisor List you will find a list of Mentors. If no mentors have been assigned to you, the system will let you know.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / GradesFirst / GradesFirst User Guide, for students / Identifying your mentor

question: How do I request to take my final exam at SAR?
ground_truth: To request to take your final exam at SAR, you must submit a Final Exam Request through Accommodate by the deadline established each semester. First, check the final exam schedule on the UWF website or in your course syllabus. Then sign in through myUWF and search for 'SAR Accommodate – Student Portal.' Select the 'Test Requests' tab, click 'New Test Request,' select your course, choose the test date and time that matches your final exam schedule, add any notes if needed, and submit your request. You will receive an email once your request is approved or denied.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / Student Accessibility Resources / Testing Accommodations / SAR Final Exams

question: What should I do first if I'm experiencing issues with ArcGIS Pro crashing when working on Argo Apps?
ground_truth: First, review the steps you made that led to the error or issue to get a better understanding of what occurred. Then, review provided course documentation, including any announcements or discussion topics from the course instructor, TA, or fellow students. If those steps don't resolve the issue, you can refer to software help documentation and online searching. Additionally, for ArcGIS Pro crashing specifically on Argo Apps, check your hardware (ensure you're using a PC or laptop, not a tablet or Chromebook), internet connection (wired/cable is optimal), and ensure your GIS project files and data are stored on the S drive rather than Google Drive or H drive.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / GIS at UWF / GIS User Training / 6. Get Help Faster

question: What do I need to do to request temporary accommodations for a medical condition?
ground_truth: To request temporary accommodations, you must: (1) Submit a Temporary Services Application at https://uwf-accommodate.symplicity.com/public_accommodation/, (2) Schedule an appointment with the Student Accessibility Resources (SAR) staff by emailing sar@uwf.edu or calling 850.474.2387, and (3) Provide supporting medical documentation from a licensed or certified professional on professional letterhead that states your condition, explains the functional limitations in the academic setting, and states what accommodations you will need.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / Student Accessibility Resources / Temporary Accommodations

question: How do I activate my MyUWF and ArgoNet account?
ground_truth: To activate your MyUWF and ArgoNet account, go to my.uwf.edu and click 'Activate your account'. Follow the directions to provide your last name and birth date to confirm your identity. Once your identity is confirmed, click 'Activate Account' to proceed. If you are a student, faculty/staff, applicant, or alumni, you will be prompted to enter an external email address and optionally a mobile number. Then select a password option (use a randomly generated system password, generate a new password, or create your own password). UWF passwords must be 14 to 20 characters long, start with a letter, and include at least one integer or special character (!%^*).
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / MyUWF / Activating your MyUWF/ArgoNet Account

question: How can I tell if a website URL is actually legitimate and not a scammer's fake version?
ground_truth: You should check the address bar carefully to verify the domain name. Legitimate UWF websites will have 'uwf.edu' at the beginning of the URL. Be aware that scammers can create similar-looking URLs - for example, a hyphen instead of a period (like 'learnmore-uwf.edu' instead of 'learnmore.uwf.edu') makes it invalid. Also check for redirects by verifying the address bar shows the site you intended to visit, avoid clicking shortened links (except Confluence links which start with 'confluence.uwf.edu'), and you can hover over links to see their actual URLs before clicking.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / Computer Security / Determining the Legitimacy and Security of a Website

question: How do I request a prerequisite override if I've already completed the required prerequisite at my home institution?
ground_truth: You should set an appointment with an academic advisor through the Navigate application on MyUWF to request a Prerequisite Override. You may also contact the course department's academic advisor directly. You may have to provide a copy of your transcripts (may be unofficial, depending on the department).
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / Transient Students / UWF Incoming Transient Student Tutorial

question: How do I reserve the Health, Leisure, and Sports facility or the Field House for an event?
ground_truth: Visit the Recreation website at https://uwf.edu/academic-engagement-and-student-affairs/departments/recreation/membership-and-services/room-rental/ to reserve recreation and sports facilities.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / Reservations

question: Which countries does UWF block network access from, and why?
ground_truth: UWF restricts incoming and outgoing network requests from seven countries: People's Republic of China, Cuba, Iran, Democratic People's Republic of Korea, Russia, Syria, and Venezuela. These restrictions are based on a thorough assessment of historical cybersecurity data, intelligence from security agencies, and the presence of malicious activities originating from these countries. The proactive approach aims to bolster defense against potential threats and ensure smooth network functioning for the academic community.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / Computer Security / Safeguarding Network Security: Restricting Network Access to Certain Countries

question: How do I request access to ArgoApps?
ground_truth: To request access to ArgoApps, submit an access request via the ArgoApps Access Request portal. Log in with your ArgoNet credentials if prompted, read and agree to the ArgoApps Usage Agreement, and click the 'I agree' button to submit your request. Approval is typically granted within minutes, and you will receive an email notification when approved. It may take up to 30 minutes after approval for you to have access to ArgoApps.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / ArgoApps / Request Access to ArgoApps

question: How can I access Adobe Creative Suite software like Photoshop and Premiere Pro as a UWF student?
ground_truth: Adobe Creative Suite software including Adobe Photoshop, Adobe Premiere Pro, and other Adobe applications are available through ArgoApps. The software listed may be restricted to certain users based on their major, classes, department, or employment position. If you have issues accessing this software in ArgoApps or completing assignments, you should contact your instructor.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / UWF Available Software

question: What are the minimum requirements I need to check before installing a software application on my computer?
ground_truth: Before installing a software application, you should check that your computer meets the stated minimum requirements for that application, which may include a minimum amount of RAM, free space on a hard drive, or processor speed.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / GIS at UWF / Basic Computer Skills for GIS / Basic Computer Concepts for GIS

question: How do I register for courses if I'm a state employee using the State Employee Tuition Fee Waiver?
ground_truth: State Employee Tuition Fee Waiver applicants must follow these steps in order: (1) Be admitted to the University, (2) Search for courses and note start dates and credit hours, (3) Register for classes starting on the third (3rd) week of Open Registration, (4) Complete the electronic State Employee Tuition Fee Waiver form after registering but before the end of drop/add, (5) Have both student and supervisor signatures on the form, and (6) Review your balance in MyUWF. It is critical to follow these steps in order to avoid being tuition and fee liable. The State Employee Waiver program does not allow overrides into closed classes, and if you receive a capacity override for a closed class, you will be fee liable for that course.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / Registration / Tuition Fee Waivers / Using the State Employee Tuition Fee Waiver

question: Which web browsers does UWF officially recommend for taking online quizzes and interacting with eLearning courses?
ground_truth: UWF's Academic Technology Center (ATC) and Information Technology Services (ITS) officially recommend Mozilla Firefox and Safari (for Macintosh users). Respondus LockDown Browser is also recommended as a special case for improving the security of online assessments.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / eLearning / eLearning Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs)

question: How do I appeal a parking ticket at UWF?
ground_truth: To appeal a parking ticket at UWF, you must file a Level One Appeal online within seven calendar days of issuance of the citation. Log on to My.UWF.edu, search for 'parking' and click the 'Parking Transaction Portal' app. Click the 'UWF Login' button, then click 'View Your Citations' to find your citation. Click the 'Appeal' button, review the citation details and agreement, complete the Appeal Details form, and click 'Submit'. Your appeal will be sent to UWF Parking Services and a copy should be sent to your email. Decisions will be posted in Building 91 and in the Parking Transaction Portal within seven calendar days.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / Parking / Appealing a Parking Citation (Level One Appeal & Level Two Appeal)

question: Who should I contact if I experience sexual harassment or gender-based discrimination at UWF?
ground_truth: You should contact Aurora Osborn, the Interim Director of Title IX Programs, in Building 19 at (850) 474-2914, via email at aosborn@uwf.edu, or visit uwf.edu/titleix for detailed information about reporting Title IX incidents and receiving support services.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / Anti-Harassment Associate (AHA) Certification Guide / Local Resources - Anti-Harassment Associate (AHA)

question: How do I unzip a file after downloading it for my GIS coursework?
ground_truth: To unzip a file after it has been downloaded, locate the zipped folder you want to unzip. You can either open the zipped folder and drag the file or folder to a new location to unzip a single file or folder, or press and hold (or right-click) the folder, select Extract All, and follow the instructions to unzip all contents. Be sure to pay attention to where you save the extracted files and save them to your dedicated drive and working folder for GIS.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / GIS at UWF / GIS User Training / 1. File Management

question: How do I access the Training Services Portal to complete Canvas training as an instructor?
ground_truth: To access the Training Services Portal, login to Canvas, click the Help link in the Canvas Global Navigation menu, and then click the Training Services Portal link. You will need to authorize Canvas and Bridge to have access to your account by clicking the Authorize button on both screens.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / eLearning / eLearning Help for Faculty / Canvas Help for Instructors / Canvas Training for Faculty

question: Is UWF participating in any Air Force JROTC programs, and if so, what is the program called?
ground_truth: Yes, UWF is an Air Force JROTC Flight Academy, Chief of Staff Private Pilot Scholarship program partner in summer 2025.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / AFJROTC Flight Academy Student Guide

question: How do I get started with the AMS Flight School at UWF?
ground_truth: To get started with the AMS Flight School, you'll need to take the steps outlined in the AMS Flight School guide. For specific information about getting started, you should direct your questions to AMS Flight School at Peter Prince Field Airport (2R4), 5600 North Airport Rd. Milton, FL 32583, by calling 850.623.4704, or visiting amsflightschool.com.
source: UWF Public Knowledge Base / AFJROTC Flight Academy Student Guide / 2) AMS Flight School
